          },
          "datePublished": "2025-02-15",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Respected Sir/mam\nI am writing to express my dissatisfaction with the behaviour and teaching methods and   curriculum activity  Moreover there is lack of participation of students in all activities\nI kindly request you to consider our concerns and take necessary steps to address them.\n*Thanks and regards*",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Bal Bharati Public School - Manesar"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "PRAMOD KUMAR SINGH"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-12-23",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "EXTRAORDINARY PERFORMANCES BY CLASS 1 KIDS IN A SIMPLE SETUP - 21st Dec 2024\n\nPositives:\n1. We witnessed an amazing performance by the Class 1 students on Presentation Day (21st December 2024). It was truly spectacular, with every child giving more than 100%! Incredible efforts all around. Kudos to the students for their enthusiasm and brilliance, and a big round of applause to the teachers for their commendable dedication to preparing each child so well.\n\n2. Exceptional work by both the teachers and students!\n\nRecommendations:\n\n1. The seating arrangement for parents could have been more thoughtfully planned to ensure better visibility and comfort for everyone.\n\n2. A dedicated space for parents or others who wish to take photos/videos during the show should be arranged. This would prevent disruption for those who prefer to watch their kids perform live without obstructions.\n\n3. The drama dialogues could have been presented in Hindi to better reflect the spirit of Rani Laxmibai’s story. Using English diluted the cultural and emotional essence of the narrative. While we understand the emphasis on English as a medium in schools, it’s not necessary to impose it in every aspect. If the intent was to showcase English proficiency, a Shakespearean drama would have been a more fitting choice. Performances like these are an opportunity for children to connect with their history and heritage. Schools should promote English as a language of communication, not as a symbol of literacy or intellectual superiority.\n\nThanks.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
